    "For instance, Basecamp 105 claims to have ten times the data of all comparable public databases, reportedly sourced through metagenomic sequencing of samples from diverse ecosystems around the planet, and is therefore likely to be more sequence-diverse.",
    "This may enhance generalisation capabilities of large protein sequence models.",
    "Overall it is likely that there is less 'low-hanging fruit' for capability development in this category than others, but this may be outweighed by the scale of resources and investment available, and the particularly strong commercial incentives.",
